Description: Round-topped limestone stela divided into three registers: 1 - Winged sun-disc with uraei. 2 - Scene of Psamtek I offering to Horus and Isis. 3 - Seven rows of Hieroglyphic text. Large blank area at the bottom.
Curator's comments: Leahy, JEA 74 (1988) pp. 183-199 Being studied as part of PhD by Elisabeth Greifenstein (University of Wuerzburg).
Associated names: Named in inscription & portrayed: Psamtek I
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Sheikh Ali Abd-el-Hai el-Gabri
